HEADWORD: molal
<hw>molal</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Being at a
concentration with the designated number of moles (of solute) per 1000
grams of solvent; <as>as, an 0.5 <ex>molal</ex> solution of glycerol in
water</as>. Compare <er>molar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
